Dr. Martel estimates that 90% of the patients who wish to die are grateful to their treating doctors for not fulfilling their wishes when the palliative care team alleviated their pain.
However, it must be said that palliative care is definitely not all-powerful in the treatment of pain.
According to Elsie Monereau, director of palliative care at the Society for Home palliative care in the Greater Montreal area, patients are prevented from treating pain in 8% of cases.
At the very end of life, doctors often use palliative sedatives, which the patient sleeps until the moment of a cut, either at the time of impact or permanently given the sedative.
We cannot pretend that we do not perceive this part of suffering.
The patient, who will not get rid of the pain, will have an increasing possibility of access to palliative sedatives.
