It will come as no surprise, then, that the articles of the Constitution were often voted unanimously.
The commentators further commented that one of the few disputes that day revolved around... hours of prayer, when some members of the committee were of the opinion that the hours in the meeting room were not properly arranged.
The text, which was voted on last night, consists of 234 articles.
The subject of general attention, Article 2, remains ultimately consistent with the 1971 version of the Constitution and states that "the principles of sharia law are the main source of law".
Salafist parties, for whom the introduction of Islamic law is one of the fundamental requirements, hoped to replace the term "principle" with the term "rule", which would allow for stricter enforcement.
